<p>I'm running a small AngularJS application which gets data from a Web API 2 REST Service. Now I want that AngularJS automaticly takes the current windows user's credentials to send it to the Web API where i can determine if the current user is allowed to access the requested data.</p>  <p>There are tutorials how I can implement this on the serverside but not in AngularJS. Is it even possible or do i need a login form ?</p>  <p>I need a good starting point where I can start gaining informations of how windows authentication works in angularjs together with Web API 2.</p>  <p>EDIT:</p>  <p>I forgot, there was something i found, but it did not work out for me. I set the withCredentials in AngularJS like this:</p>  <pre><code>angular.module('resources.default', ['ngResource']) .factory('DefaultResource', ['$resource', '$cacheFactory', function ($resource, $cacheFactory) {     var baseUrl = "http://localhost:7020/api";     var baseParams = {};     var baseOptions = {         save: {             method: 'POST',             headers: {                 'Content-Type': 'application/json;charset=UTF-8',                 'Accept': '*/*'             }         },         get: {             cache: false,             headers: {                 'Expires': '-1',                 'Cache-Control': 'no-cache',                 'Pragma': 'no-cache',                 'If-Modified-Since': '0'             }         },         query: {             cache: false,             isArray: true,             headers: {                 'Expires': '-1',                 'Cache-Control': 'no-cache',                 'Pragma': 'no-cache',                 'If-Modified-Since': '0'             }         }     };      return function (extUrl, extParams, extOptions) {         var finalUrl = baseUrl + extUrl;          var finalParams = angular.extend(baseParams, extParams);         var finalOptions = angular.extend(baseOptions, extOptions);         return $resource(finalUrl, finalParams, finalOptions);     }; }]).config(['$httpProvider', function ($httpProvider) {     $httpProvider.defaults.withCredentials = true; }]); </code></pre>  <p>But when debugging the Web API controller there isn't an authenticated user: <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/tjq0H.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/tjq0H.png" alt="User.Identity in the controller"></a></p>